10.body: Go to Manage tab Under Services, select the service to be edited In the "Resources" panel: Turn the switches to ON for all resources which need to be marked as "in-use" during the service Examples: For a laser hair removal appointment, the multi-laser room and GentleMax Pro device For a body sculpting appointment, the body sculpting room and a truSculpt device

11.body: From the Front Desk view Go to the Clients tab "Merge Clients" button Search for first client profile -> Select profile Search for second client profile -> Select profile Choose preferred information for each of the following: ["First Name", "Last Name", "Email", "Mobile", "Birth Date", "Emergency Contact Name", "Emergency Contact Relationship", "Emergency Contact Phone", "Address"] Click/tap the "Merge Clients" button at the bottom of the page
11.title: How to: Merge client profiles

12.body: Navigate to client's appointment Go to the checkout panel Complete their "basket" (make sure all the products and services for the transaction are on the ticket) Select the "Other" payment method in the bottom-right of the checkout panel From the "Payment Type" dropdown menu, select "Package" (Optional) Add a detailed description !!! IMPORTANT !!! Change the dollar amount to whatever is required (i.e. If a $350 service is being covered by a voucher, input $350) Click/tap the green "Charge $#.##" button The amount is now deducted from the total transaction (if it covers the full value of the transaction, the sale will close and no further action is required) Any outstanding amount can now be collected via any additional payment method (Card, Cash, Gift Card, Credits, or another form of Other payment) Collect other payment (if necessary) and complete the transaction
12.title: How to: Missing voucher payment

13.body: Start from the LabcorpLink login page Log in to the account View the Dashboard Click on the "Results Search" button From the Results Search page , enter identifying information into the form Click the "Search" button at the bottom of the screen Select the instance of labs to be printed Click the "Print" button near the top-right of the page Using the "Print" button, click or tap on the dropdown arrow Select "Download" Enter a proper file name when prompted Save the file to the "Downloads" folder on the local machine (the computer you're using) Open Outlook application Select the "New Mail" button In the "To" field, enter the patient's email address Add a cc recipient, subject line, and body text (if needed) Attach the downloaded file (from the Downloads folder) Click the "Send" button
13.breadcrumbs: How to: Print lab results » To send:
13.title: To send:

15.body: This guide assumes that you have a client with a pre-standing appointment already scheduled and on the books, potentially even completed (i.e. you're signing them up for a membership to pay for the day's treatment). If you do not, then create one for the client you'll be setting up with membership. For services, add the treatment they have received or will be receiving that day. Add a "Membership Initiation" SERVICE to their appointment Go to "Checkout" In the top-right, select the uppermost 3-dot menu (in line with the client's name) Click "Edit appointment" On "Search for a service", click and then type "Memb" Select "Membership Initiation" from the dropdown In the bottom-right, deselect the checkbox for "Resend Confirmation" Click or tap "Update Appointment" Have the client complete their forms (steps listed below) After adding the "Membership Initiation" service: Grab iPad (or have client use the front desk iPad) Open "Duo" app (if not already open) Tap "Check In ->" Enter client phone number (or email) Tap "Complete Forms" Hand iPad to client (or have them continue using the front desk iPad) Add an "Initiation Fee" PRODUCT to their bill Add the Membership (with appropriate tier) PRODUCT to their transaction Ensure their primary service (i.e. PicoWay) is changed to the "for Tier #" option Charge a partial amount equal to their membership tier (i.e. $199.00 for Tier III members) Charge the remainder via card, cash, etc.

15.title: Steps

4.body: From the Front Desk view Go to the Business Manager page (gear icon) On the side bar menu, select Products Click on the "New Product" button Name the product as follows: {BRAND} - {ITEM} (Example: "SkinCeuticals - Cell Cycle Catalyst") For retail products, ensure the checkbox for "Charge tax on this item" is checked Add a "Product Price" (Optional) Select a supplier (Optional) Select a category (Optional) Enter a brand
4.title: How to: Create a product

5.body: Gear icon Services tab New service Make the service name "Treatment for Tier # Member" Replace "Treatment" with the name of the treatment Replace "#" with the corresponding tier number For category, select "Membership Services (Tier #)" Replace "#" with the actual tier number Set the default price equal to one month of membership for the tier (e.g. $199.00) Set the duration to the appropriate amount of time for the treatment Go to the Manage tab Services tab Find the standard (non-membership) treatment and select it Find the standard treatment commission amount (default price * commission amount) For example, if treatment is normally $250 @ 10% then $25 Navigate to the service that was created Select the service While in this menu, deselect (turn OFF) the "Bookable online" checkbox! Divide the commission amount by the membership tier's price $25 commission / 19900 membership = 0.125628... Multiply the result by 100 0.125628... * 100 = 12.5628... Round the product to 2 decimal places 12.5628... = 12.56 or 12.57 Enter the result as the commission amount
5.breadcrumbs: How to: Create a member service » To set the commission amount
5.title: To set the commission amount

6.body: Manage menu -> Services tab -> Service item -> Resources tab Turn on the switches which correspond to the treatment being provide Example: laser hair removal treatment room, multi-laser room laser device, gentlemax pro

7.body: Gear icon Services tab "New Service" button If the service to be created is a new type which is not covered by an existing category, first select the "New Category" button and create the category first before proceeding with a service Enter a service name Select a service category Click "Create Service" Required: Set a Default Price, Duration Optional: Set Processing, Finishing, and Transition Times Duration = Default (if a solid time block) OR part one of the appointment (such as time to apply numbing) Processing Time = Numbing time or equivalent Finishing Time = Second part of appointment, if split by processing time Transition time = Time that practitioner is busy afterward but client is free (such as cleaning of the room or spinning blood for labs) Optional: Add a service product (e.g. Syringes of peptides, units of tox) IF A SERVICE PRODUCT IS USED, IT NEEDS TO BE CREATED SEPARATELY AND THEN ASSIGNED Click/tap the "Save changes" button in the bottom-right of the menu
7.breadcrumbs: How to: Create a service » Create the service itself
7.title: Create the service itself

8.body: Go to Manage tab Under Services, select the service to be edited In the "Overview" panel (which pops up by default when a service is selected) Add a "Commission Override" with the desired rate as a percentage Use the "Bookable online" checkbox to enable/disable this functionality in the booking portal
8.breadcrumbs: How to: Create a service » Add service details (set commission rate and/or make bookable online)
8.title: Add service details (set commission rate and/or make bookable online)

9.body: Go to Manage tab Under Services, select the service to be edited In the "Staff" panel: Turn the switches to ON for all staff (by name) who should be assignable and allowed to carry out the procedure. This will also enable them to be shown as a practitioner option when a client is booking online
